  "base_path": "/towing-with-motorcycle",
  "content_id": "c79ef546-c71f-4ab5-aebc-5a3783f1fcf1",
  "description": "You can tow some small trailers using motorbikes of 125cc or more",
  "details": {
    "body": "\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>You can use motorbikes with an engine size of 125cc or more to tow small trailers.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Your motorbike has to be clearly and permanently marked with its ‘kerbside weight’.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Kerbside weight is the weight of the vehicle without passengers or any load but with a full tank of fuel and filled up with the necessary oils, water and fluids.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The trailer must be no more than 1 metre wide and must be clearly and permanently marked with its unladen weight.</p>\n\n<p>When the trailer is loaded it must weigh no more than 150 kilograms or 2/3 of the kerbside weight of the motorbike - whichever is lighter.</p>\n\n<p>When hitched, the distance between the end of the trailer and the rear axle of the motorbike must be no more than 2.5 metres.</p>\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
